body_text.text:
During seasonal outbreaks of bronchiolitis from November through March in North America, respiratory syncytial virus (RSV) is identified as the etiologic agent in up to 80% of hospitalized children7 (Table 33.1
). Other respiratory viruses that cause a largely indistinguishable syndrome include human rhinoviruses, parainfluenza viruses, human metapneumoviruses, coronaviruses, adenoviruses, influenza viruses, enteroviruses, and human bocaviruses.8, 9, 10, 11 The yearly cycles of respiratory virus circulation are depicted in Fig. 33.1
.
